arrests and deportation flights=E2=80=94is immigration. Right now, 55 perce=
nt of voters approve of the way Trump is handling immigration, with 40 perc=
ent saying they =E2=80=9Cstrongly approve=E2=80=9D of his immigration actio=
ns. It=E2=80=99s not just Republicans, either. Roughly half of independents=
 approve of Trump=E2=80=99s immigration moves so far, and almost a quarter =
of Democrats do, too. Meanwhile, more than a third of Hispanic voters expre=
ssed support for
Trump=E2=80=99s immigration policies, although a majority of Hispanics (62 =
percent) are opposed.

=C2=A0

As for the raft of executive orders Trump signed on his first day in office=
, voters generally support them by a 10-point margin (52 percent support ve=
rsus 42 percent opposed). Opinions get mixed, though, when voters are asked=
