x;">It=E2=80=99s hard to think of a worse time for a Democrat to go on a bo=
ok tour, but
<strong>Gretchen Whitmer </strong>is out there braving the cold. The Michig=
an governor, and putative presidential wannabe, has just published a =E2=80=
=9Cyoung adult=E2=80=9D version of her book <em>True Gretch</em>, a slim au=
tobiography with =E2=80=9Clessons for anyone who wants to make a difference=
=2E=E2=80=9D (<em>True Gretch</em>, which=20=
sounds like a spoof Puck headline,=20=
really is an inexcusable title for a memoir=E2=80=A6) Whitmer showed up Mon=
day on <em>CBS This Morning</em> to hawk the book, and offered a few lesson=
s on how to
talk like a Democrat who isn=E2=80=99t totally sure what to say after her p=
arty got shoved into a locker by <strong>Donald Trump</strong>.</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bott=
om:0px;">Hosts <strong>Vladimir Duthiers</strong>, <strong>Gayle King</stro=
ng>, and <strong>Tony Dokoupil</strong> asked about Trump, his swift crackd=
own on illegal immigrants, the threat of tariffs, and the governor=E2=80=99=
s take on the state of the Democratic Party. Whitmer, an occasionally
talented politician, responded with some pablum=E2=80=94the same stuff you=
=E2=80=99re hearing a lot from Democrats right now, in state capitals and t=
he halls of Congress. A few examples:</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom=
:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><em>=E2=80=9CI am=
 not out looking for fights. I am always looking to collaborate.=E2=80=9D</=
em></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><em>=E2=80=9CI am focused on moving forward and fin=
ding common ground where
we can.=E2=80=9D</em></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p=
><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><em>=E2=80=9CI am not against tar=
iffs, per se, but we have to be strategic.=E2=80=9D</em></p><p style=3D"mar=
gin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;=
">The interview wasn=E2=80=99t bad or embarrassing. It was just rote, cauti=
ous, and forgettable=E2=80=94a manifestation of where Democrats are right n=
ow in the first week of Trump 2.0, which looks very different from his firs=
t tour in office. Back
then, the American public was stunned, Trump was unprepared, and Democrats =
were in permanent attack mode. It was a moment that gave rise to a new gene=
ration of Democratic politicians, including Whitmer, who defined themselves=
 almost completely as Trump antagonists.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;marg=
in-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Indeed, =
for half a decade, Democrats from city councils to presidential debate stag=
es were running mostly just to stop Trump, competing
to out-outrage one another in the process. What were Democrats actually <em=
>for</em>? Certain values, sure: multiculturalism, the middle class, health=
care, higher taxes on billionaires, abortion rights. But at every turn, the=
y were stymied, <em>terrified</em> of offending lefty interest groups or ac=
tivists and the surplus elites who staff campaigns. At the same time, the p=
arty seemed to live in fear of pissing off wealthy donors, suburban centris=
ts, and lunchbucket labor types alike.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin=
-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">As a conse=
quence, Whitmer-style equivocation has become the <em>lingua franca</em> of=
 the party. This familiar manner of speech=E2=80=94<em>on the one hand, on =
the other</em>=E2=80=94is inescapable now that Trump and Republicans run th=
e government, with high approval ratings for not just the president but als=
o many of the policies he=E2=80=99s implementing.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;m=
argin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">Take Whitmer=E2=80=99s response on <em>This Morning</em=
> to the ICE raids unfolding around the country right now. =E2=80=9CWe do h=
ave a problem at the southern border. I have sent my national guard down to=
 the border to help with surveillance under both a Biden administration and=
 a Trump administration,=E2=80=9D she said. =E2=80=9CBut we also need to tr=
eat people with dignity and follow the law. As we see this continue to play=
 out, we will assess how we conduct ourselves in the state of Michigan.=E2=
=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;mar=
gin-bottom:0px;">You can=E2=80=99t blame Whitmer or her colleagues for play=
ing it safe. Democrats haven=E2=80=99t been<em> this</em> unsure about whic=
h way the wind was blowing since, what, 2005? At least in 2017, they had Tr=
ump to howl at. Now? =E2=80=9CWe will assess how we conduct ourselves in th=
e state of Michigan.=E2=80=9D To be fair, what else is an ambitious Democra=
t to say? She isn=E2=80=99t the only one playing four corners. In Californi=
a, <strong>Gavin
Newsom</strong> is making nice with Trump because he has to=E2=80=94the sta=
te needs federal disaster relief after the brutal wildfires here in Los Ang=
eles.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;">I also took note last week of a proactive email sent to repo=
rters from the office of <strong>J.B. Pritzker</strong>, the governor of Il=
linois, after news broke that ICE would possibly be starting its illegal im=
migrant roundups in Chicago. The memo included helpful
background, but Pritzker=E2=80=99s office was <em>not</em> interested in ta=
lking about immigration. Instead, the email flagged how Pritzker =E2=80=9Ci=
s getting big things done=E2=80=9D for working families in Illinois, helpin=
g small business owners, and protecting disabled workers. =E2=80=9CIf you a=
re interested in more information on immigration law in Illinois, please le=
t us know and we can share some more information later,=E2=80=9D the note e=
xplained. =E2=80=9CBut, as you can see below, he has a busy week ahead bein=
g Governor of
Illinois!=E2=80=9D</p></div>
